Change happens. change happens in roleplay.<br>
<br>
Meledi has had to change her opinion about Mhordel. Originally, Mhordel was suspect, the assassin hired by Littany to kill her guide to the Necropolis (Zildrax however won that bout).. But people can change, and now Meledi, a neutral bard, accepts Mhordel, who has in her eyes been reformed by a certain druid lady. Sadly Meledi recognizes that many of her friends may not share her views.  <br>
<br>
Change happens in guilds, and in alliances.<br>
<br>
In regard to the Fellowship, Elven Blades acted with integrity. They decided to change their membership rules in a way that did not allow them to continue in the Fellowship and they resigned.  Fellowship rules are not always ideal, but they represent a voted upon / accepted compromise that lets us draw a line of what is evil ( after much debate I might add ). Guilds in the Fellowship have the right to join and withdraw as they need, it is a voluntary association. Winds of Destiny made a similar decision a while ago, and also withdrew from the Fellowship.  How the guild makes the decision is totally outside the charter of the Fellowship, each guild is automous and does their own process.<br>
<br>
Change can be hard. <br>
<br>
It can hurt as old friends have differing views.  I know this well running a guild.  Sometimes the only thing you can do is agree to disagree and in the worst case, agree that if you cant live with the majority decision you need to move on.  Its not always about black and white, wrong or right, sometimes its just about what works and what cant be made to work. <br>
<br>
*quietly toasts the changewinds*  But without change there is no challenge, no growth, no new songs to sing.  <p><img border=0 src="http://www.leagueofhonour.com/images/members/meledi-sig.jpg" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pailq>Pail Q</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/12/03 6:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=110>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Change..</span><hr size=1> <br>
